From ecc87e849e81a2541048869d3c89f519e46ebe40 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vivian Wang <wangruikang@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 21:51:31 +0800
Subject: [RUYI PATCH] FROMLIST: ACPI: tables: Add missing #include
 <asm/fixmap.h>

drivers/acpi/tables.c uses NR_FIX_BTMAPS without including
<asm/fixmap.h>. This isn't a problem for existing archs, but would be
when ARCH_HAS_ACPI_TABLE_UPGRADE is enabled for RISC-V. Add the missing
include.

Signed-off-by: Vivian Wang <wangruikang@iscas.ac.cn>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20260616-riscv-acpi-table-upgrade-v1-1-45902d2dedf9@iscas.ac.cn
Signed-off-by: Han Gao <gaohan@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 drivers/acpi/tables.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/acpi/tables.c b/drivers/acpi/tables.c
index 57fc8bc56166..c127da7fa32a 100644
--- a/drivers/acpi/tables.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/tables.c
@@ -22,6 +22,7 @@
 #include <linux/initrd.h>
 #include <linux/security.h>
 #include <linux/kmemleak.h>
+#include <asm/fixmap.h>
 #include "internal.h"
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_ACPI_CUSTOM_DSDT
-- 
